  "prompt": "What hotel in Varanasi would be safe for unmarried couples, without the harassment of police, hotel staff, and moral police?",
  "response": "In Varanasi, as in many parts of India, certain hotels are known for being more accepting of unmarried couples. To ensure a safe and hassle-free stay, consider looking for hotels that explicitly state they are couple-friendly. Popular online booking platforms such as OYO Rooms, Treebo, and FabHotels often have filters or categories for couple-friendly hotels. Here are a few options that have been known to welcome unmarried couples:\n\n1. **OYO Rooms**: Many OYO hotels across Varanasi are couple-friendly and offer privacy and comfort. Ensure you check the hotel reviews and confirm their couple-friendly policy when booking.\n\n2. **FabHotels**: FabHotels also has a selection of properties in Varanasi that are known for having a liberal policy towards unmarried couples. \n\n3. **Treebo Hotels**: Similar to OYO and FabHotels, Treebo often lists properties that are couple-friendly. Always check the specific hotel details to confirm their policy.\n\n4. **Hotel Madin**: A reputed hotel known for good services and hospitality; while staying here as an unmarried couple, ensure you carry valid government-issued ID proofs.\n\n5. **Hotel Suryauday Haveli**: Located near the banks of the Ganges, a good option for couples looking for a serene stay. Confirm their couple-friendly policy before booking.\n\nHere are a few tips to further ensure a smooth experience:\n- **Carry Valid IDs**: Always carry valid government-issued ID proofs such as Aadhar card, Passport, or Driver\u2019s license.\n- **Pre-book Online**: Booking online through reputed platforms usually ensures a smoother check-in process.\n- **Check Reviews**: Go through recent reviews from other unmarried couples for insights into their experiences.\n- **Contact the Hotel Directly**: Prior to booking, call the hotel to confirm their policy regarding unmarried couples.\n\nRemember, as long as you have a valid government ID and are consensual adults, staying together is your right. Avoid overly secluded places and choose well-reviewed and reputed hotels for a safe and comfortable stay.",
